sgl-kernel GPU architecture prune for DGX Spark GB10 (SM121).

Problem:
  Upstream sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt hardcodes a large gencode list that
  builds CUDA binaries for every Blackwell variant (sm_100a B200,
  sm_103a Grace-Blackwell server, sm_110a, sm_120a RTX Blackwell,
  sm_121a GB10) PLUS an unconditional sm_90 baseline. On aarch64 +
  CUDA 13.x the effective list is:

      sm_90, sm_100a, sm_103a, sm_110a, sm_120a, sm_121a

  Six binaries per translation unit, of which only sm_121a is ever
  selected by the CUDA loader on a DGX Spark. The rest is dead weight
  that multiplies sgl-kernel build time 5-6x.

  (sm_90a is a separate matter — see sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch. This
  patch leaves sm_90a compilation as-is since it is scoped to the FA3
  branch, which only activates when FA3 itself is enabled.)

Fix:
  1. Remove the unconditional "-gencode=arch=compute_90,code=sm_90"
     baseline from the SGL_KERNEL_CUDA_FLAGS list. GB10 has compute
     capability 12.1 — the loader never selects sm_90 SASS, it selects
     sm_121a. Keeping sm_90 just wastes ptxas time.

  2. Strip sm_100a, sm_103a, sm_110a, sm_120a and sm_101a out of the
     CUDA >= 12.8 / >= 13.0 expansion block. Keep sm_121a as the only
     Blackwell arch emitted, and keep the "--compress-mode=size" nvcc
     flag (it is not arch-specific).

Expected impact:
  - sgl-kernel (excluding FA3) binaries shrink from 5-6 variants per TU
    to 1 → ptxas stage collapses proportionally.
  - Build time for the sgl-kernel layer drops roughly by the same
    factor, assuming the host is ptxas-bound (it is on GB10 cold builds).
  - Resulting wheel is a fraction of the upstream size (fewer cubins
    packed).
  - IMAGE IS NOW GB10-ONLY. Do not deploy this wheel to any other
    Blackwell or Hopper SKU — they will find no matching SASS and fall
    back to PTX JIT which will silently fail for sm_121a PTX.

Drift risk:
  If scitrera / sgl-kernel refactor the CUDA_FLAGS list layout, both
  hunks of this patch may need to be regenerated. patch --dry-run in
  the Docker build step catches this at build time with a clear error
  rather than producing a silently-broken image.

Apply to: sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt in the sglang source tree, inside
the Dockerfile builder stage (BEFORE the sgl-kernel `uv build --wheel`
step, since the arch list is consumed at CMake configure time).

Upstream source: sgl-project/sglang tag v0.5.10

--- a/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -136,7 +136,8 @@
     "-O3"
     "-Xcompiler"
     "-fPIC"
-    "-gencode=arch=compute_90,code=sm_90"
+    # dgxarley sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch: baseline sm_90 removed.
+    # GB10 is sm_121a; sm_90 SASS would never be loaded. See patch header.
     "-std=c++17"
     "-DFLASHINFER_ENABLE_F16"
     "-DCUTE_USE_PACKED_TUPLE=1"
@@ -216,29 +217,22 @@
 
 endif()
 
+# dgxarley sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch: SM121-only Blackwell expansion.
+# Upstream emits sm_100a (B200), sm_120a (RTX Blackwell), sm_103a (Grace-
+# Blackwell server), sm_110a (other Blackwell), sm_121a (GB10), sm_101a.
+# On the DGX Spark fleet only sm_121a is ever loaded by the runtime; the
+# rest is 5-6x dead weight per TU. We keep the --compress-mode=size global
+# nvcc flag because it is not arch-specific.
 if ("${CUDA_VERSION}" VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL "12.8" OR SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_SM100A)
-    list(APPEND SGL_KERNEL_CUDA_FLAGS
-        "-gencode=arch=compute_100a,code=sm_100a"
-        "-gencode=arch=compute_120a,code=sm_120a"
-    )
-    # refer sm_121, sm_110 and sm_101 description  https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/156176
     if ("${CUDA_VERSION}" VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL "13.0")
         list(APPEND SGL_KERNEL_CUDA_FLAGS
-            "-gencode=arch=compute_103a,code=sm_103a"
             "--compress-mode=size"
         )
         if (CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR STREQUAL "aarch64")
             list(APPEND SGL_KERNEL_CUDA_FLAGS
-                "-gencode=arch=compute_110a,code=sm_110a"
                 "-gencode=arch=compute_121a,code=sm_121a"
             )
         endif()
-    else()
-        if (CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR STREQUAL "aarch64")
-            list(APPEND SGL_KERNEL_CUDA_FLAGS
-                "-gencode=arch=compute_101a,code=sm_101a"
-            )
-        endif()
     endif()
 endif()
 
